# 🎤 Voice-Enabled FAQ Chatbot

This project is a **voice + text-based FAQ chatbot** built using **Streamlit, OpenAI, SpeechRecognition, and gTTS**.  
It allows users to **ask FAQs via typing or voice input**, and the bot replies with **text + speech output**.

---

## 🚀 Features
- Ask FAQs by typing or speaking.
- Upload an audio file (wav/mp3/m4a) for automatic transcription.
- Text-to-Speech (TTS) responses with `gTTS`.
- Maintains chat history.
- Uses OpenAI GPT for natural FAQ matching.

---

## 📂 Project Structure
voice-faq-chatbot/
│── app.py # Main Streamlit application
│── requirements.txt # Dependencies
│── README.md # Documentation

---

## ⚙️ Setup & Installation
1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/voice-faq-chatbot.git
   cd voice-faq-chatbot

 2. Create a virtual environment and install dependencies:
     pip install -r requirements.txt

3.Add your OpenAI API key:
   export OPENAI_API_KEY="your_api_key_here"

## ▶️ Run the App
streamlit run app.py

##🛠️ Future Scope
- Add multilingual FAQ support.

- Fine-tune on custom company data.

- Deploy on cloud (Streamlit Cloud / Heroku / AWS).

- Integrate with WhatsApp or Slack for enterprise use.

